This package implements the Perforce (Helix) RPC client protocol from scratch.

Portions of `protocol.py` — specifically the Perforce login "Mangle" cipher
(the `_otox`, `_getdval`, `_mangle_block` and `_mangle_encrypt` functions and
the `_O` / `_PR` / `_S0` / `_S1` S-box constants) — are a Python port of
`Mangle.java` from the open-source Perforce P4Java client
(https://github.com/perforce/p4java). That ported code is used under the
following BSD-3-Clause terms, reproduced from P4Java's LICENSE.txt as required
by condition 1.

